{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/init(_:length:helperText:isOutlined:status:autofocus:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/init(_:length:helperText:tableName:bundle:isOutlined:status:autofocus:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/body"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/obfuscationCharacter","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/placeholderCharacter"],"anchor":"Type-Properties","title":"Type Properties","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/Length","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/Status"],"anchor":"Enumerations","title":"Enumerations","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/View-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSPinCodeInput"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"text":"Layouts","level":2,"anchor":"Layouts","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"outlined"}]},{"text":" layout: A minimalist input with a transparent background and a visible stroke outlining the field.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This style may be interesting for contexts other than form pages, e.g. when inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in a header (search field), or in a selection\/filtering feature in a product catalog","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not outlined"}]},{"text":" (default): An input with a subtle background fill and visible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Best suited for dense layouts or to enhance visibility.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component provides 3 layouts for the input: 4 boxes, 6 boxes or 8 boxes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A helper text can be used to support text to convey additional information about the input field, such as how it will be used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Error status","level":2,"anchor":"Error-status","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Error status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or expected formatting."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border, error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the input (mandatory)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This state helps users quickly identify and correct mistakes by explaining what went wrong and, when possible, how to fix it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The input remains editable, encouraging users to revise their input without starting over."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The error state must be triggered by an explicit validation (submission, API response), and not in real time with each keystroke."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This can occur either because the entered code does not match the expected code, because the user entered an expired or already used code,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or finally if the maximum number of attempts has been exceeded."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Specific design guidelines","level":2,"anchor":"Specific-design-guidelines","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the context of a PIN code input, in addition to the input’s “Error” UI rendering, it is essential to also include an “Alert” component"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(also in its “Error” status) in the interface."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Particular cases","level":2,"anchor":"Particular-cases","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" component supports autofill feature of values like OTP code.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example if the user receives a message with inside a code the system can extract, the keyboard can suggest to the user to fill it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the digits fits the component, it will be filled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the digits are longer, they will be truncated.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the digits are shorter, they will be filled, letting other fields empty.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The copy\/paste feature is also available and has the same behavior.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Technical considerations","anchor":"Technical-considerations","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For some cases, on phones screens or with 8 boxes in iPhone, you may need to use a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ScrollView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to embed the component and let user move it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","    OUDSPinCodeInput($value,","                     length: .eight,","                     helperText: \"Enter your secret code sent to your phone\")","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note also the exposed ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"value"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be updated when all digits are written.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The content of the fields is vocalized by Voice Over; the placeholders (defined in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/obfuscationCharacter","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/placeholderCharacter","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":")","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are not vocalized to let users know what they wrote.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The component gets only numeric values, not letters or symbols, only numbers.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Depending on the component configuration, autofocus can still be used when the component appears, and focus is moved to the next field as digits are entered.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example if Voice Over is enavled, the autoficus is disabled.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The component and its digit fields are vocalized with internal wording.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using the error status, provide a clear, concise error message explaining what went wrong and, when possible, how to fix it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(for example: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“The code you entered is invalid. Try again.”","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use helper text to communicate additional guidance (for example: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“Check the 6‑digit code sent by SMS”","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"), and keep this text short so it remains easy to vocalize","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and understand.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The value with the code","    @State private var pinCode: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ By default, the PIN code input displays only 6 boxes","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode)","","    \/\/ It can have also up 4 or 8 boxes, with an helper text","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode, length: .eight, helperText: \"Enter your 8 secret digits\")","","    \/\/ The component can be used in error contexts","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode, length: .six, status: .error(message: \"The OTP code you entered is not correct\"))"]},{"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-pin-code-input","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"text":"Orange Compact","anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}]},{"text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"text":"Wireframe","anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.2.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Version"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.4.0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Since"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"symbolKind":"struct","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents16OUDSPinCodeInputV","title":"OUDSPinCodeInput","platforms":[{"beta":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"15.0"},{"beta":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSPinCodeInput"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSPinCodeInput"}],"role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudspincodeinput"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"PIN code input is a UI element that allows to capture short, fixed-length numeric codes, typically for authentication or confirmation purposes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as a four, six or eight-digit personal identification number (PIN)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"PIN code input is presented as a series of individual input fields or boxes, each representing a single digit, to enhance readability and encourage accurate input,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"while supporting smooth keyboard navigation and secured input masking if needed."}],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/Controls":{"title":"Controls","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"}],"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/controls","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components can be used for "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"controls","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"inputs","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"article"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSPinCodeInput/init(_:length:helperText:isOutlined:status:autofocus:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/init(_:length:helperText:isOutlin